      "rationale": "Formal equivalency mapping between experimental and computational input parameters is not required at MRL 2. Qualitative alignment between CFD boundary conditions and experimental setup has been documented in the Test Conditions factor assessment above."
    }
  ],
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/cou1-cpb-decision-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team has reviewed all 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors in the context of the MRL 2 designation for this COU. Seven factors were formally assessed; six were scoped out as not required at MRL 2. Of the seven assessed factors, six achieved their required level without qualification. The Numerical Solver Error factor was assessed at achieved level 2 against a required level of 3; however, the team determined that the convergence indicators observed across all five operating points — residuals reaching 1×10⁻⁵ to 1×10⁻⁶, mass-flow imbalance below 0.01%, and consistency with eight years of institutional experience on equivalent rotating blood-contacting device simulations — provide sufficient indirect evidence that iterative solver error is not a material contributor to prediction uncertainty for the hemolysis index. This judgment is corroborated by the GCI analysis, which confirms that discretization error (the dominant numerical error source) is below 5% at all operating points, and by the favorable output comparison results (mean absolute error 11.4%, no systematic bias). The team acknowledges that a formal iterative error budget would be required to formally close level 3 for this factor, but concludes that the totality of quantitative and qualitative evidence supports the conclusion that model credibility is sufficient for the intended regulatory use. The relative hemolysis index RH < 1 acceptance criterion is satisfied at all five operating points. The decision is Accepted.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
